1
00:00:01,830 --> 00:00:03,540
I'm so excited.

2
00:00:03,740 --> 00:00:05,340
Superhero movies are always so exciting.

3
00:00:05,460 --> 00:00:06,340
Yeah.

4
00:00:06,341 --> 00:00:08,459
Especially sequels. The hype is real.

5
00:00:08,460 --> 00:00:09,460
Yeah.

6
00:00:09,980 --> 00:00:12,940
Saeki, who's your
favorite superhero?

7
00:00:13,140 --> 00:00:14,590
A superhero, huh?

8
00:00:15,180 --> 00:00:17,259
- What about you, Wataru?
- Me?

9
00:00:17,260 --> 00:00:19,480
I'm a die-hard Jet fan.

10
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:21,370
I knew it. I totally called it.

11
00:00:26,020 --> 00:00:27,020
During summer break,

12
00:00:27,340 --> 00:00:29,069
even on days we weren't
visiting film locations,

13
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:33,319
we'd still hang out, watch
movies, and grab food.

14
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:35,000
Just spending time together doing nothing.

15
00:00:35,060 --> 00:00:36,760
Have you decided yet?

16
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,220
Yeah.

17
00:00:39,580 --> 00:00:41,250
But it's a secret.

18
00:00:41,420 --> 00:00:43,580
What?
Now you've got me curious.

19
00:00:46,420 --> 00:00:47,560
The trailers are starting.

20
00:00:51,380 --> 00:00:55,400
But then, out of nowhere, it would hit me.

21
00:00:58,800 --> 00:00:59,640
Hey.

22
00:00:59,641 --> 00:01:01,069
What are you smiling at?

23
00:01:01,070 --> 00:01:02,780
Nothing. It's nothing.

24
00:01:03,180 --> 00:01:04,020
Come on.

25
00:01:04,021 --> 00:01:05,220
Now you've got me curious.

26
00:01:06,980 --> 00:01:08,760
No, really.
I just thought...

27
00:01:12,060 --> 00:01:14,500
you look cute when you pout.

28
00:01:18,460 --> 00:01:19,560
I like you.

29
00:01:21,660 --> 00:01:23,159
Ouch!

30
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:24,680
Look straight ahead. Watch the screen.

31
00:01:25,380 --> 00:01:26,380
Okay, okay.

32
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,580
Wandering through doubts and confusion,
they slowly search for answers.

33
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:37,760
Where will their future lead them?

34
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:49,780
In the end, I couldn't focus at all.

35
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:55,239
Maybe we hyped it up too much
because it was a sequel.

36
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,240
Huh?

37
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:57,030
Huh?

38
00:01:57,031 --> 00:02:00,030
Well, you sighed so loudly,
I thought you were disappointed.

39
00:02:00,530 --> 00:02:01,699
Oh...

40
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:02,900
Yeah, I guess so.

41
00:02:03,870 --> 00:02:05,920
It wasn't bad, though.

42
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:09,279
But maybe it's because
they changed directors for this one.

43
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,280
Yeah.

44
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:15,160
But there are other movies to see this
summer. Let's look forward to the next one.

45
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:16,880
Yeah.

46
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:21,290
By the way,
where are we going for our next pilgrimage?

47
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,220
Oh, let me see...

48
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:27,960
The tonkatsu place from the middle of the
movie, and the beach from the final scene.

49
00:02:28,350 --> 00:02:31,150
Let's start with the closer one,
the tonkatsu place.

50
00:02:31,310 --> 00:02:33,150
Ah, that tonkatsu place.

51
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:36,660
The one that saved the protagonist
from the depths of despair, right?

52
00:02:36,740 --> 00:02:37,979
Man, I'm starving just thinking about it.

53
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:39,280
When should we go?

54
00:02:39,580 --> 00:02:41,140
Let me think.

55
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:44,240
I have work shifts coming up.
How about the 10th?

56
00:02:45,420 --> 00:02:46,700
The 10th, huh?

57
00:02:50,370 --> 00:02:52,360
Hmm? What's wrong?
You don't seem very excited.

58
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:55,400
Oh, do you already have plans that day?

59
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,060
No.

60
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:58,700
I'm free that day.

61
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:03,260
I was just wondering... Does that mean
we won't see each other until the 10th?

62
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,380
Huh?

63
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,010
Come on,
that's not that far away.

64
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:08,456
Besides, we'll see each other
at the national mock exam on the 6th.

65
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,160
Yeah, I guess so.

66
00:03:10,350 --> 00:03:12,390
But to me right now,
that feels like forever.

67
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:15,120
Oh, really?

68
00:03:18,690 --> 00:03:19,980
Wataru, you know...

69
00:03:20,060 --> 00:03:21,659
You always pout when you're embarrassed.

70
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:22,990
I am not pouting.

71
00:03:23,030 --> 00:03:24,280
And I'm not embarrassed.

72
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,080
You totally have a grumpy face right now.

73
00:03:28,790 --> 00:03:30,020
I'm hungry.

74
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:31,620
Let's go eat.

75
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:34,790
Being with Saeki is just as fun as always.

76
00:03:34,990 --> 00:03:37,050
Even though nothing has really changed,

77
00:03:37,130 --> 00:03:38,460
What do you want to eat?

78
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,380
I can't help but feel...

79
00:03:43,980 --> 00:03:45,200
Ginger pork.

80
00:03:47,180 --> 00:03:48,280
How should I put it...

81
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:51,700
Hey, Wataru.
How've you been lately?

82
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:55,640
My heart just won't stop fluttering.

83
00:03:56,580 --> 00:03:58,339
What's that about? Wataru, you pervert!

84
00:03:58,340 --> 00:03:59,880
No, he's just in heat.

85
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:02,920
What about you guys?

86
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:05,590
Great, we're doing great.

87
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,259
Man, it's boiling hot every day.

88
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:09,039
And I'm just practicing judo all day.

89
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:10,560
Do you have club
practice today too, Hiraoka?

90
00:04:10,580 --> 00:04:11,580
No, today's my day off.

91
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:17,920
Then do you want to go to karaoke
after the mock exam?

92
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:19,550
Oh, yeah! Let's do it.

93
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:21,620
- Are you in?
- Wataru, you're coming too, right?

94
00:04:21,880 --> 00:04:23,280
Oh, do you have work?

95
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,930
No work today, so I'm in.

96
00:04:27,470 --> 00:04:29,639
Karaoke? Can I come along too?

97
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:30,929
Uh, it's Asada.

98
00:04:30,930 --> 00:04:31,940
What's with the "uh"?

99
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:33,940
Nothing!
I was just saying "uh-huh, sure!"

100
00:04:33,980 --> 00:04:34,860
Classic Guchi.

101
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:36,190
Quick on your feet.

102
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,400
That's not a compliment.

103
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:40,400
So, what's the plan?
Who's paying?

104
00:04:40,730 --> 00:04:43,419
- Hmm...
- Let's decide by our exam scores.

105
00:04:43,420 --> 00:04:44,620
A score battle, huh?

106
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:45,920
I like it! I like it! I like it!

107
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:47,580
- Huh?
- Sorry, I'm just...

108
00:05:02,900 --> 00:05:05,330
How should I put it...

109
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,030
My heart is fluttering a bit.

110
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:47,000
"My Summer Of You"
(Episode 3)

111
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:53,660
♪ When we first met, I never imagined ♪

112
00:06:54,030 --> 00:06:59,000
♪ That a day of parting
like this would ever come ♪

113
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:03,670
♪ Making good things better ♪

114
00:07:03,710 --> 00:07:06,830
♪ No, it's all in the past now ♪

115
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:12,760
♪ We were merely piling
up the moments we shared ♪

116
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:18,640
♪ Exhausted in body and soul ♪

117
00:07:18,650 --> 00:07:26,150
♪ What you loved was
nothing but my illusion ♪

118
00:07:29,210 --> 00:07:32,709
Wataru, I queued up the next song for you.

119
00:07:32,710 --> 00:07:35,080
Whoa! What is it?

120
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,700
(A Little Love Song)

121
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:39,540
I hope you find love this year.

122
00:07:39,580 --> 00:07:40,860
Shut up.

123
00:07:42,370 --> 00:07:46,170
♪ Among the countless
stars in the vast universe ♪

124
00:07:46,650 --> 00:07:50,590
♪ In the wide world of this blue planet ♪

125
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:55,030
♪ This tiny love will find its way ♪

126
00:07:55,110 --> 00:07:59,610
♪ To you on your tiny island ♪

127
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:26,169
Man, I'm exhausted.

128
00:08:26,170 --> 00:08:26,970
A table for four?

129
00:08:26,971 --> 00:08:28,590
- Please sit anywhere.
- Okay.

130
00:08:28,790 --> 00:08:30,109
Isn't this booth a bit too big for us?

131
00:08:30,110 --> 00:08:31,929
- This one?
- Yeah, seriously.

132
00:08:31,930 --> 00:08:35,299
Alright, let's eat, eat, eat!

133
00:08:35,300 --> 00:08:36,300
Cola, cola.

134
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:38,309
Cola again?

135
00:08:38,310 --> 00:08:41,059
- Yep, cola again.
- I think I'll get the hamburger steak today.

136
00:08:41,060 --> 00:08:41,930
I feel that.

137
00:08:41,931 --> 00:08:43,689
- Oh?
- What's up?

138
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:46,399
Hey, isn't that Saeki over there?

139
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:47,270
Are you a cat person or a dog person?

140
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:48,110
Birds.

141
00:08:48,150 --> 00:08:49,189
Hamsters.

142
00:08:49,190 --> 00:08:50,329
Hamsters?

143
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:51,629
Do you have a hamster?

144
00:08:51,630 --> 00:08:52,869
I used to have one.

145
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:53,870
Oh, what color was it?

146
00:08:53,871 --> 00:08:54,890
Grey, I think.

147
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:58,510
Whoa, he's with two girls.

148
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:01,989
The popular-kid energy
over there is insane.

149
00:09:01,990 --> 00:09:04,200
Excuse me, there's a girl right here too.

150
00:09:04,370 --> 00:09:05,370
Huh? Where?

151
00:09:06,430 --> 00:09:08,340
Do you need to get your eyes checked?

152
00:09:08,750 --> 00:09:11,089
- Seriously.
- Your prescription must be off.

153
00:09:11,090 --> 00:09:12,349
Wait, really?

154
00:09:12,350 --> 00:09:14,529
Wait, isn't Hiraoka a girl?

155
00:09:14,530 --> 00:09:15,890
- No way!
- Stop joking around.

156
00:09:16,090 --> 00:09:17,760
- She has zero game.
- But still...

157
00:09:17,770 --> 00:09:19,599
- No way, no way, no way.
- Come on, that's not true.

158
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,659
Honestly, Wataru looks
more like a girl than she does.

159
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:23,130
Huh? Me?

160
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:24,670
No way.

161
00:09:29,330 --> 00:09:31,230
That brings back memories.

162
00:09:31,970 --> 00:09:37,870
In seventh grade, when Wataru had soda for
the first time, it shot right out of his nose.

163
00:09:38,610 --> 00:09:40,250
I remember! It came out of both nostrils.

164
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:41,980
It sprayed so far.

165
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:43,949
It did not shoot out of my nose!

166
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:46,249
Maybe a slight exaggeration?

167
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:47,250
Just a little bit.

168
00:09:47,890 --> 00:09:52,890
But it just means
you were so innocent and cute back then.

169
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:55,719
Compared to the rest of us
sweaty guys in the judo club,

170
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:58,590
Wataru is still pretty cute.

171
00:09:59,410 --> 00:10:02,109
I'm just pure-hearted, unlike you guys.

172
00:10:02,110 --> 00:10:03,619
Oh? Even though your heart is fluttering?

173
00:10:03,620 --> 00:10:04,809
I told you, it's not!

174
00:10:04,810 --> 00:10:06,890
Are you still on that?

175
00:10:08,290 --> 00:10:09,290
He's seriously so cute.

176
00:10:09,310 --> 00:10:11,129
- What was its name?
- Huh?

177
00:10:11,130 --> 00:10:12,130
What was it again?

178
00:10:12,131 --> 00:10:15,130
- I forgot.
- No way, you just said it.

179
00:10:16,170 --> 00:10:18,160
But I think I get what you mean.

180
00:10:18,530 --> 00:10:22,629
In elementary school, I
always hung out with boys too.

181
00:10:22,630 --> 00:10:24,550
But gradually, it became
harder to talk to them.

182
00:10:25,850 --> 00:10:28,889
But with Toda, it's totally fine.

183
00:10:28,890 --> 00:10:29,960
Why is that?

184
00:10:30,390 --> 00:10:35,830
Wataru is just a boy at
heart. A pure-hearted boy.

185
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:37,010
Pure-hearted boy.

186
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:38,300
Pure-hearted boy.

187
00:10:38,301 --> 00:10:39,740
I'm going to get refills.

188
00:10:40,350 --> 00:10:41,450
- Same thing?
- Yeah.

189
00:10:41,490 --> 00:10:42,490
Thanks.

190
00:10:43,170 --> 00:10:46,630
- Toda is basically the nation's little brother.
- Hey.

191
00:11:07,850 --> 00:11:10,530
Hey, cut it out.

192
00:11:10,810 --> 00:11:13,340
You guys are definitely not praising me.

193
00:11:13,460 --> 00:11:15,150
- Pure-hearted boy.
- Pure-hearted boy.

194
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:20,470
Uh...

195
00:11:20,670 --> 00:11:23,010
Oh, my brother's calling me to come home.

196
00:11:24,070 --> 00:11:26,220
- I'll head out first.
- Ah, I should probably head back too.

197
00:11:26,230 --> 00:11:27,510
I have to get up early tomorrow.

198
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:29,450
What are you guys going to do?

199
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:32,540
Aren't you going to get dessert?

200
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:33,670
Well...

201
00:11:33,671 --> 00:11:35,311
I have time. I can stay and eat with you.

202
00:11:35,690 --> 00:11:36,819
Thanks.

203
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:38,220
I'll decide what to get right away.

204
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:43,400
Hey, Wataru.

205
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:44,970
Could you pay for these, please?

206
00:11:45,370 --> 00:11:46,510
Sure, no problem.

207
00:11:46,950 --> 00:11:47,950
Thanks!

208
00:11:49,050 --> 00:11:50,110
- We'll head out first. Bye!
- Bye.

209
00:11:50,130 --> 00:11:51,690
Bye. Talk to you later.

210
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,870
- Have you decided yet?
- Not yet.

211
00:12:04,270 --> 00:12:05,990
You're still thinking about it, aren't you?

212
00:12:06,730 --> 00:12:08,300
Huh? The dessert?

213
00:12:08,350 --> 00:12:09,870
No, not that.

214
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:10,930
Saeki and his friends.

215
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:13,000
You've been staring
over there this whole time.

216
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:14,570
No, I haven't.

217
00:12:15,020 --> 00:12:16,020
If you say so.

218
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:19,650
I was wondering...

219
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:22,040
if the person Saeki likes is in that group.

220
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:26,380
So you still don't know
who it is, do you?

221
00:12:28,740 --> 00:12:30,240
Are you still on about that?

222
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:31,449
I told you, I don't know.

223
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:33,670
- Really?
- Really.

224
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:39,310
Even if I did, it's not like I'd
go around gossiping about it.

225
00:12:39,820 --> 00:12:40,820
True.

226
00:12:41,130 --> 00:12:42,340
That makes sense.

227
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:44,960
Oh, by the way.

228
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,899
Did you take any photos
during your pilgrimage?

229
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:47,919
Well, yeah, I did.

230
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:50,960
- Let me see!
- No way, I'm not showing you.

231
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:53,730
Come on, why not?
I just want to see the scenery.

232
00:12:53,770 --> 00:12:55,140
- Yeah, right. Nice try.
- Hand it over! Come on!

233
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:56,279
You just want to look at handsome guys.

234
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:58,179
I can't deny that.

235
00:12:58,180 --> 00:12:59,480
Wataru.

236
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,520
You're here too.

237
00:13:03,490 --> 00:13:04,590
Yeah...

238
00:13:05,060 --> 00:13:06,920
I'll text you about the 10th.

239
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:09,580
I'll head out first.

240
00:13:16,660 --> 00:13:18,959
Did something happen between you and Saeki?

241
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:20,010
Huh...?

242
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:22,459
You guys are going on
another pilgrimage, right?

243
00:13:22,460 --> 00:13:24,970
He seemed so excited about it before,

244
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,940
but he seemed so distant just now.

245
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:32,850
We're just getting pork cutlets.
It's normal to be casual about it.

246
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:36,540
But Saeki...

247
00:13:36,810 --> 00:13:38,960
He's been stealing glances
at you this whole time.

248
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:40,180
Really...?

249
00:13:40,190 --> 00:13:43,400
So I was wondering
if he has you on his mind.

250
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:49,399
Wait, did you just smile?

251
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:51,500
- What's that about?
- Huh? I didn't smile.

252
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,330
- Come on, just order already.
- I know, I know.

253
00:13:55,370 --> 00:13:56,439
Hurry up.

254
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,670
Give me a second.

255
00:13:59,260 --> 00:14:00,480
Hmm...

256
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:04,440
- You're going to order pudding again, aren't you?
- I'd love to, but...

257
00:14:05,740 --> 00:14:06,740
A parfait, huh?

258
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:08,490
- Want to share?
- Sure, why not?

259
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:20,860
Wow, that looks delicious.

260
00:14:21,540 --> 00:14:23,400
- Let's eat!
- Let's eat!

261
00:14:23,910 --> 00:14:25,179
I'll go with the sesame dressing.

262
00:14:25,180 --> 00:14:26,420
Hmm...

263
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:28,440
Then I'll use the onion dressing.

264
00:14:31,410 --> 00:14:33,300
Wow, this looks so good.

265
00:14:43,210 --> 00:14:44,460
It's delicious!

266
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:45,960
This is amazing.

267
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:48,240
- It's so good, it's incredible!
- Yeah.

268
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:51,390
This is the best pork cutlet I've ever had.

269
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:54,680
I knew it would be good,
but it was totally worth the trip.

270
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:56,000
It definitely was.

271
00:14:56,620 --> 00:14:57,620
You know,

272
00:14:57,900 --> 00:15:01,299
food in movies and on TV
always looks so much better.

273
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,300
I know, right?

274
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:03,980
I have a weak spot
for simple food.

275
00:15:04,060 --> 00:15:04,860
Like rice balls.

276
00:15:04,861 --> 00:15:06,900
Oh, I totally get that.

277
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:11,450
But seriously, this is so good.

278
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,460
What's wrong?

279
00:15:19,660 --> 00:15:20,979
You have a grain of rice on your face.

280
00:15:20,980 --> 00:15:22,000
Huh? Rice?

281
00:15:22,290 --> 00:15:23,290
Where?

282
00:15:24,380 --> 00:15:25,380
Right here.

283
00:15:50,780 --> 00:15:51,880
How embarrassing.

284
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:56,700
It's so cool sitting in the exact same spot
as they did in the movie.

285
00:15:56,740 --> 00:15:57,540
Yeah.

286
00:15:57,541 --> 00:15:59,306
Oh, we should take a
picture before we finish.

287
00:15:59,330 --> 00:16:00,500
Oh, right.

288
00:16:00,830 --> 00:16:02,339
Hey there, handsome fellas.

289
00:16:02,340 --> 00:16:04,980
You came here because
of "Sea of Light," right?

290
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:07,200
- Yes.
- I knew it!

291
00:16:07,940 --> 00:16:11,130
Actually, I was an extra in that movie.

292
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:14,879
The scene where the main character
cries because the cutlet is so good...

293
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:16,039
You remember that, right?

294
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:19,520
I was the clerk
looking at him with concern.

295
00:16:24,280 --> 00:16:26,610
I was just an extra,
but I accidentally stole the scene.

296
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:29,579
If you'd like,
I can take a photo of you two.

297
00:16:29,580 --> 00:16:31,960
Oh, yes, please.

298
00:16:32,380 --> 00:16:34,230
- Then we'll...
- Come on, get together. No problem.

299
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,440
Okay, I'm going to take it.

300
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:36,800
Ready, set...

301
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:37,220
Huh...?

302
00:16:37,220 --> 00:16:38,220
*Click*

303
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:39,960
*Click, click*

304
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,680
Yay!

305
00:16:49,100 --> 00:16:50,710
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you very much.

306
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:52,930
- Come back soon! Thank you.
- Thank you.

307
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:54,589
Thank you for waiting.
Table for four, right this way.

308
00:16:54,590 --> 00:16:56,760
- That's a great souvenir.
- Yeah.

309
00:16:58,440 --> 00:16:59,890
What should we do next?

310
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:02,390
Is there anything fun to do around here?

311
00:17:03,940 --> 00:17:06,199
Oh, Higashimura Park is really close.

312
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:08,619
It's only about two stops away.

313
00:17:08,620 --> 00:17:09,840
Yeah.

314
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:12,440
Wow, this brings back memories.

315
00:17:12,980 --> 00:17:14,799
Can we stop by?

316
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:15,810
Huh...?

317
00:17:16,620 --> 00:17:19,900
- Come on, let's go.
- Oh, alright.

318
00:17:19,940 --> 00:17:21,370
Great, let's go!

319
00:17:26,340 --> 00:17:29,170
Wow, it hasn't changed at all.

320
00:17:30,060 --> 00:17:32,020
I fell into this pond once.

321
00:17:32,970 --> 00:17:33,920
Why?

322
00:17:33,921 --> 00:17:38,470
Well, I think I thought
I could walk along the fence.

323
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:39,970
Are you serious?

324
00:17:40,580 --> 00:17:42,060
I can totally picture that.

325
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:44,270
Hey, you're laughing too hard.

326
00:17:45,190 --> 00:17:46,200
Geez.

327
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:49,020
Everyone treats me like a kid.

328
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:53,090
Asada even called me "the
nation's little brother" the other day.

329
00:17:54,780 --> 00:17:55,780
Really?

330
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:57,280
Yeah.

331
00:17:57,380 --> 00:17:59,470
What about you, Saeki? Have you been here?

332
00:18:00,530 --> 00:18:03,540
Oh, I think so.

333
00:18:04,820 --> 00:18:06,000
With my ex-girlfriend.

334
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:11,640
Oh...

335
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:18,780
Come to think of it, I think this is the
first time I've heard you talk about this.

336
00:18:22,470 --> 00:18:23,570
By the way,

337
00:18:24,950 --> 00:18:26,830
Wataru, are things
going well with that girl?

338
00:18:27,350 --> 00:18:28,370
Which girl?

339
00:18:29,890 --> 00:18:32,290
The one you were with at the diner.
Asada, right?

340
00:18:33,130 --> 00:18:34,349
You two stayed behind alone.

341
00:18:34,350 --> 00:18:35,320
Huh?

342
00:18:35,321 --> 00:18:37,130
It's not like that at all.

343
00:18:37,470 --> 00:18:40,029
It's just that Asada really wanted dessert,

344
00:18:40,030 --> 00:18:41,310
so I stayed to keep her company.

345
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:43,710
- Oh, I see.
- Yeah.

346
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:46,370
Hmm...

347
00:18:48,690 --> 00:18:52,590
I thought she and Wataru
looked good together.

348
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:02,000
What is with you today?

349
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:04,520
First your ex-girlfriend,
now Asada.

350
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:10,550
And another thing...

351
00:19:11,030 --> 00:19:13,960
Back at the diner,
you talked to me so casually.

352
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:19,910
Usually, when you see the person you like
having a good time with someone else,

353
00:19:19,990 --> 00:19:21,860
doesn't it make you feel uncomfortable?

354
00:19:26,950 --> 00:19:28,250
It doesn't bother me.

355
00:19:32,950 --> 00:19:34,130
Oh.

356
00:19:39,410 --> 00:19:41,010
I told you from the start.

357
00:19:43,890 --> 00:19:46,030
Just being able to tell you how I feel,

358
00:19:47,990 --> 00:19:50,170
and having you treat me normally,

359
00:19:52,506 --> 00:19:54,736
and even going on
this pilgrimage with me...

360
00:19:56,290 --> 00:19:57,790
that's more than enough for me.

361
00:20:06,550 --> 00:20:11,070
I want you to do whatever you want, Wataru.

362
00:20:20,450 --> 00:20:21,690
I get it.

363
00:20:30,390 --> 00:20:31,430
Huh?

364
00:20:32,570 --> 00:20:33,700
Someone's crying.

365
00:20:42,870 --> 00:20:44,126
- It's that little girl.
- Mommy, it hurts!

366
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:45,569
- What's wrong?
- It hurts!

367
00:20:45,570 --> 00:20:47,910
- Chiharu!
- It hurts!

368
00:20:48,750 --> 00:20:49,750
Are you okay?

369
00:20:50,930 --> 00:20:53,009
Mommy, it hurts!

370
00:20:53,010 --> 00:20:54,669
Did you fall?

371
00:20:54,670 --> 00:20:55,950
Let me see your knee.

372
00:20:56,810 --> 00:20:58,730
Ouch, that must hurt.

373
00:20:59,690 --> 00:21:01,670
Let's go over there and
put some medicine on it.

374
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,930
- Medicine...?
- Yeah.

375
00:21:09,230 --> 00:21:11,140
She seems fine now.

376
00:21:12,230 --> 00:21:13,230
Yeah.

377
00:21:15,630 --> 00:21:17,010
Her name is Chiharu, too.

378
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:19,750
Yeah.

379
00:21:21,110 --> 00:21:24,480
My name was also chosen so it
could be used for either a boy or a girl.

380
00:21:25,070 --> 00:21:26,160
I see.

381
00:21:28,630 --> 00:21:29,630
Oh.

382
00:21:29,950 --> 00:21:32,449
Come to think of it, when I was little,

383
00:21:32,450 --> 00:21:35,020
I met a crying little girl here, too.

384
00:21:36,270 --> 00:21:37,330
Really?

385
00:21:39,050 --> 00:21:42,060
She was crouching and crying,
just like that little girl.

386
00:21:43,010 --> 00:21:44,570
I couldn't just leave her.

387
00:21:46,130 --> 00:21:47,900
She said she was lost,

388
00:21:48,166 --> 00:21:50,436
so I took her to find her parents.

389
00:21:57,610 --> 00:21:59,290
Are you okay?

390
00:22:07,170 --> 00:22:09,440
But that little girl...

391
00:22:09,450 --> 00:22:10,530
Wataru.

392
00:22:13,250 --> 00:22:14,330
What is it?

393
00:22:15,270 --> 00:22:16,410
I'm sorry.

394
00:22:17,330 --> 00:22:19,370
If you don't want this,
you can push me away.

395
00:22:27,930 --> 00:22:28,930
Wait...

396
00:22:28,950 --> 00:22:30,100
What are you doing?

397
00:22:30,970 --> 00:22:31,760
What if someone comes...?

398
00:22:31,761 --> 00:22:33,800
Yeah... I know.

399
00:22:56,930 --> 00:22:58,990
He said that was enough,

400
00:23:01,910 --> 00:23:03,670
and put an end to
his feelings on his own.

401
00:23:07,610 --> 00:23:10,570
But when he expresses his
feelings to me so wholeheartedly...

402
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:16,950
Even I...

403
00:23:42,710 --> 00:23:45,500
The reason I want to return his feelings...

404
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:49,050
Maybe it's all because of summer.

405
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:49,190
(Next Episode) Once this arrangement
is over, what will become of us?

406
00:24:49,230 --> 00:24:52,590
Showing someone your room feels like
being stripped bare. It's so embarrassing.

407
00:24:52,630 --> 00:24:53,280
Thank you.

408
00:24:53,281 --> 00:24:55,209
I heard Saeki took the day off today.

409
00:24:55,210 --> 00:24:57,440
If you ever stop liking me...

410
00:24:57,670 --> 00:24:58,670
That's...

411
00:24:58,830 --> 00:24:59,830
That's...

